<br>
Oh and before you start to say it, I am not goung to PL the chanter up to 40-50 and not have a clue about the class. I actually plan on just PLing him to 16 then grouping from that point on.  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87111"><font color="Green"><font size="2"><B>Adonna Bladelore</B><BR>58 Half Elf Ranger of Karana<BR>Torvonnilous</a></font></font><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=charmroxors>Charmroxors</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#330000>(4/14/03 1:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question reguarding Int and Cha</span><hr size=1> your INT can never be high enough, until you hit the cap on INT you should still be going for items with it. your charm spells have a series of &quot;rolls&quot; they go through every tick and the mob checks them and whether or not you win is whether or not the charm breaks. the 3rd check it makes is your CHA, so having it fairly high is always a plus (the first two checks are your lvl vs. its lvl, and its magic resist).<br>
<br>
the one other stat i'd look into while making your chanter is STA, you can never have enough hit points =)<br>
<br>
 <p>Charmroxors<br>
