<br>
The problem came when the mez caps came into place. You found that your mez/charm became impossible on most mobs. And you needed to carry around 2 sets of gear, normal and resist gear. It became time to refocus on the direction of your character’s stats. I started to focus on Mana and resists. Everyone makes there own choices at that point. Cause it's the gear at that point that drives you. <br>
<br>
I guess I am an enchanter who won’t give up my Charisma. I still keep it in the 220’s and buff the +50 Cha buff. Why? Cause I loved it when I charmed a named dragon in western wastes and freaked out my guild.   <br>
