<br>
I can tell you without any doubt that the single most dramatic factor affecting charms for me has been the &quot;resistance factor&quot; of the NPC.  If an NPC is not naturally high MR and has been tashed and malo'd, it almost always holds until max duration of CoD.  If the NPC is naturally high MR or if its resists haven't been reduced by debuffs, duration is extremely erratic.<br>
<br>
If you have lower CHA and no TD3, you're only going to compound this problem.  If you have debuffed the resistances of a mob that isn't highly MR, but you aren't high in CHA or have AA pts to help, you'll once again get very erratic durations.<br>
